HEADWORD: Curvity
<hw>Cur"vi*ty</hw> <pr>(k?r"v?-y?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>curvitas</ets>, from <ets>curvus</ets> bent: cf. F.
<ets>curvit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The state of being curved; a
